 address inequalities, and advocates for placing Muslim families at the heart of policy solutions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aMuslim familieszGreat Britain. 0aMuslimszGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z9783111299655oZDB-23-BUPP40uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781529221732?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781529221732423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781529221732/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPb2024